OL,3,CDelayed post causing 'nightmare' for
OL,4,Cfrustrated Cornish town
OL,6,F"I just don't think senior managers,
OL,7,Fof what is now a privatised firm, have
OL,8,Freally been putting in the resources
OL,9,Fto make sure the frontline services
OL,10,Fare operating properly.
OL,12,F"And what you're seeing now, in places
OL,13,Flike Helston and The Lizard, is a
OL,14,Fservice which is under such incredible
OL,15,Fstress, and the frontline workers are
OL,16,Fparticularly feeling it at the moment."
OL,18,FMr George says he has written to the
OL,19,Fchief executive of Royal Mail, and is
OL,20,Fawaiting a response.
